---
/**
 * rest-api/0007 · Figure 2 — the Cache-Control directives map: grouped by the
 * three questions it answers (how long fresh? who may store? reuse rules?).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source HTML (figure + svg + figcaption). Lives as an
 * .astro component for the kebab-case-SVG reason. No arrowhead markers, so no
 * local <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Cache-Control directives grouped: lifetime (max-age, s-maxage), storage scope (public vs private, no-store), and reuse rules (no-cache, must-revalidate, stale-while-revalidate)"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">CACHE-CONTROL · THREE QUESTIONS IT ANSWERS</text
            >

            <rect x="10" y="32" width="200" height="206" rx="9" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#d8d4c8"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="110"
                y="52"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">HOW LONG FRESH?</text
            >
            <rect x="22" y="64" width="176" height="36" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text x="110" y="80" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700"
                >max-age=N</text
            >
            <text x="110" y="93" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >fresh for N seconds</text
            >
            <rect x="22" y="106" width="176" height="40" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text x="110" y="122" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700"
                >s-maxage=N</text
            >
            <text x="110" y="135" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >shared caches only · wins</text
            >
            <text x="110" y="172" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >Expires = legacy absolute</text
            >
            <text x="110" y="186" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >timestamp; max-age</text
            >
            <text x="110" y="200" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >supersedes it (no skew)</text
            >

            <rect x="220" y="32" width="200" height="206" rx="9" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#d8d4c8"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="320"
                y="52"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">WHO MAY STORE?</text
            >
            <rect x="232" y="64" width="176" height="40" rx="6" fill="#eef2f5" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="320"
                y="80"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">public</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="93" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >any shared cache may store</text
            >
            <rect x="232" y="110" width="176" height="40" rx="6" fill="#eef2f5" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="320"
                y="126"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">private</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="139" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >browser only · per-user</text
            >
            <rect x="232" y="156" width="176" height="40" rx="6" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="320"
                y="172"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">no-store</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="185" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >never write to any cache</text
            >

            <rect x="430" y="32" width="200" height="206" rx="9" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#d8d4c8"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="530"
                y="52"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">REUSE RULES?</text
            >
            <rect x="442" y="64" width="176" height="40" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text x="530" y="80" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700"
                >no-cache</text
            >
            <text x="530" y="93" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >store, but 304-check first</text
            >
            <rect x="442" y="110" width="176" height="40" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
            ></rect>
            <text x="530" y="126" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700"
                >must-revalidate</text
            >
            <text x="530" y="139" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >once stale, no serving stale</text
            >
            <rect x="442" y="156" width="176" height="40" rx="6" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="530"
                y="172"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">stale-while-revalidate</text
            >
            <text x="530" y="185" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#244a2e"
                >serve stale, refresh in bg</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        A still-fresh response is reused with zero contact with the origin — that's the whole win. <code
            >no-cache</code
        > is the confusingly named one: it <em>does</em> cache; it just won't serve without a 304 check.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
